that the machine learning methods used work on program abstractions makes the approach generic and suitable for other imperative languages (e.g., FORTRAN, which is also widely used in scientific computing). The application of the approach to other languages would require changes to the tool described in Section 4 in order to account for some specific syntactical patterns of a particular programming language. Nevertheless, most of the abstraction features identified and described in Section 4 are also applicable to other imperative languages since they capture common aspects like control flow, data layout, data dependencies, etc.
